elements.name: Interestholder
elements.documentation: Citizens and companies that could be (adversely) influenced by the initiative of another person or by a decision of an authorized supervision.

elements.name: Algorithm keeper
elements.documentation: Manager responsible for the development and management of an algorithm.

elements.name: Process owner
elements.documentation: Manager responsible for the application of an algorithm in a process.

elements.name: Representative of the people
elements.documentation: Member of Local Council or Member of States-Provincial, who performs a controlling function on the governing body.

elements.name: Executor
elements.documentation: Employee who carries out a process that leads to decision-making by the governing body.

elements.name: Role
elements.documentation: Responsibility of the behavior exhibited by a business actor.

elements.name: Actor
elements.documentation: Organizational unit (function employee, department, organization).

elements.name: Business object
elements.documentation: A physical or conceptual object that is relevant from the point of view of the business.

elements.name: Representation
elements.documentation: An observable or tangible form of the information carried by a business object.

elements.name: Business Function
elements.documentation: A collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria (typically required business resources and/or competencies), closely aligned to an organization, but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

elements.name: Algorithm database
elements.documentation: Records data that result from algorithms.

elements.name: Algorithm register
elements.documentation: Software for recording and making data about an algorithm available.

elements.name: Corporate website
elements.documentation: Software for managing and accessing web content of the governing body.

elements.name: Data catalog
elements.documentation: Software for registering and making available metadata of a dataset.

elements.name: Nationwide algorithm catalogue facility
elements.documentation: Software for unlocking information from algorithms of all govering bodies in the Netherlands.

elements.name: User Interface viewing
elements.documentation: Viewing via webbrowser.

elements.name: User Interface registration
elements.documentation: Registration via webbrowser.

elements.name: Role / Access management
elements.documentation: Granting access to the registration function.

elements.name: API Interface data catalog
elements.documentation: Provides API functionality for querying datasets from the data catalog.

elements.name: API Interface publication
elements.documentation: Provides API functionality for algorithm publishing in the corporate website and the nationwide algorithm publishing facility.

elements.name: API interface registration
elements.documentation: Provides API functionality for algorithm registration in the algorithm registration.

elements.name: Backend API application
elements.documentation: Provides API functionality for registration, querying and publishing.

elements.name: Application component
elements.documentation: Part of an information system.

elements.name: Application function
elements.documentation: Internal behavior of an application component.

elements.name: Registration
elements.documentation: A data object, an information unit.

elements.name: Digital accessibility
elements.documentation: Temporary decision digital accessibility of government

elements.name: A good information position
elements.documentation: Information is available, usable and resistant. Information is presented in an understandable way to the customer (both inside and outside the organization), so that he/she is in control of the use of his/her data. Customers must be able to identify incorrect registration of their data.

elements.name: The AR is open
elements.documentation: Change processes are based on open tenders and the resulting solution complies with open standards.

elements.name: The AR is compliant
elements.documentation: The provision of information meets the requirements of legislation and regulations.

elements.name: Publicity of algorithms
elements.documentation: Public algorithms in control

elements.name: The AR exchanges data openly
elements.documentation: Open exchange: The application exchanges on the basis of open standards.

elements.name: Use JSON / GEOSJON
elements.documentation: Use JSON / GEOSJON: If the service link is via API, then the standard JSON/GEOJSON is used.

elements.name: Describe API
elements.documentation: API description: The description of the API conforms to the standard OpenAPI Specification for describing REST APIs.

elements.name: Document API
elements.documentation: Documentation API: The API setup and documentation complies with the standard REST API Design Rules for structuring and documenting REST APIs.

elements.name: Develop for AR an open standard
Controllability
elements.documentation: I want to be able to carry out my audit task on the functioning of the governing body.

elements.name: Minimum requirement for publicity
elements.documentation: I want to clarify which minimum set of descriptions of the algorithm is necessary.

elements.name: Explainability
elements.documentation: I want to understand how the outcome of the algorithm came about and what data was used.

elements.name: Trust
elements.documentation: I want to know if using the algorithm does not conflict with my interests.

elements.name: Every algorithm used in a decision that can affect me has been described
The fundamental for each algorithm used in decisions is described
The minimum necessary data has been recorded for each algorithm
The operation and the data used are described for each algorithm used in my work
AR standard includes operation and data
Constraint
elements.documentation: A factor that limits the realization of goals.

elements.name: Principle
elements.documentation: A guiding statement about the (company) design.

elements.name: Goal
elements.documentation: A high-level declaration of intent, direction or desired end state.

elements.name: Driver
elements.documentation: An external or internal condition that motivates an organization.

elements.name: Outcome
elements.documentation: Endresult.

elements.name: Stakeholder
elements.documentation: A role that represents the interests of an individual, team, or organization.

elements.name: Value
elements.documentation: The relative value, usefulness or importance of a concept.
